The paper proposes a novel algorithm for learning fair representations, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the trade-off between utility and fairness, which is a common theme in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the alignment of representations, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the fairness of algorithms, which is related to the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
